    "date": "2018-03-09",
    "comment": "Rationale: Using a constutitive Liprin a3 knockout (KO), Wong et.al. shows that Liprin a3 participates in synaptic vesicle exocytosis. In synaptophysin-pHluorin imaging experiments, KO neurons showed a reduction in the total amount of exocytosis. This was rescued by reintroduction of Liprin a3.\n\nThe KO is characterized in figure 2, showing absence of the protein in western blot using 3 different antibodies.. Experimental description: Primary mouse hippocampal cultures were generated from newborns as previously described (20), and all analyses were performed at DIV 14-17.",
